review_data: Reviewed in the United States on July 2, 2021
name: Brooke L McLymond
title: Cheaper to buy single cans at Walmart
review: I love these drinks and was excited to see they came in a 12 pack on Amazon!They sell them at Walmart in single cans but often are sold out or only have a few.Problem is, it's cheaper to buy individual cans at Walmart, even if you get the 5% off with subscribe and save.It leaves me scratching my head that I can't find these anywhere in a 12 pack for less than buying them individually at Walmart.

review_data: Reviewed in the United States on June 24, 2021
name: Sean McGuigan
title: Not impressed
review: I bought these thinking it was a 12 pack and how disappointed I was when I received the order. However, I immediately put them in the fridge to enjoy later. I love coconut so I was excited to try this brand but was super turned off by the watery flavor that did not taste like coconut at all. I drank two and let my husband drink the rest. I will never buy again or recommend to anyone else. The price is too steep, the cans way too small and the taste not special enough.

review_data: Reviewed in the United States on September 6, 2021
name: Lindsay M.
title: Shockingly good
review: I went into trying these protein shakes with a healthy amount of skepticism -- low carb, chocolate, AND 20g of protein?Seems way too good to be true, and so many shakes I've tried in the past have had weird textures, cloyingly sweet flavoring, or hidden sugars.NOT these.The texture is creamy, the chocolate amount just perfect, and they really are what they say.I was so surprised how much I enjoyed drinking these.The packaging is just the right size to fill you up and not leave you hungry in an hour, if you are using this as a meal replacement or after-workout meal.I honestly can't say enough good things about this shake.I can honestly say they are the best protein shakes out there that I have tried, and I have tried a lot.5/5 stars, highly recommend!
